''Other Goelet Buildings include the [[Judge Building]] on 5th Avenue'' [[File:Goelet Building 900 Broadway.jpg|thumb|upright|Goelet Building]]
The '''Goelet Building''' is a historical structure located at 900 [[Broadway (Manhattan)|Broadway]] on the corner of East 20th Street, in the [[Ladies' Mile Historic District]] of [[Manhattan]], [[New York City]]. It was designed by [[Stanford White]] of [[McKim, Mead & White]], and built in 1886–1887.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gray|first=Christopher|title=Streetscapes {{!}} Broadway and 20th Street Same Parents, No Resemblance|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/01/15/realestate/15scap.html?pagewanted=all|accessdate=7 March 2014|newspaper=The New York Times|date=January 15, 2006}}</ref> The building was enlarged in 1905–06 by [[Robert Maynicke|Maynicke & Franke]].
