{{Korean name|Park}} {{Infobox person |name = |image = |caption = |birth_date = October 25, 1948 |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |other_names = |known_for = President of the [[Boy Scouts of Korea]] |spouse = |nationality = |module3 = {{Infobox Korean name | hangul = 박건배 | hanja = 朴健培 | rr = Bak Geon-bae | mr = Pak Kŏn-bae | image = | caption = | child = yes}} }}
'''Park Kun-bae''' ({{Korean|박건배|朴健培}}; born October 25, 1948) served as President of the [[Boy Scouts of Korea]], and as a member of the [[World Scout Committee]].
In 1999, Park was awarded the 277th ''[[Bronze Wolf]]'', the only distinction of the [[World Organization of the Scout Movement]], awarded by the World Scout Committee for exceptional services to world Scouting,<ref>https://www.scout.org/BronzeWolfAward/list complete list</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scout.org/en/content/download/11624/94866/file/Triennial_Report_EN_5.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-03-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090327024400/http://www.scout.org/en/content/download/11624/94866/file/Triennial_Report_EN_5.pdf |archivedate=2009-03-27 |df= }}</ref> as well as the highest distinction of the [[Scout Association of Japan]], the [[Golden Pheasant Award]].<ref>reinanzaka-sc.o.oo7.jp/kiroku/documents/20140523-3-kiji-list.pdf</ref>
