{{italic title}} {{refimprove|date=May 2012}} '''''Pay without Performance: The Unfulfilled Promise of Executive Compensation''''' is a 2004 book by professors of law [[Lucian Bebchuk]] and [[Jesse Fried]] on the power of corporate executives in the United States to influence their own pay and of the structural defects in corporate governance that grant them this power.
==Reception== The book has been praised by mutual fund founder [[John C. Bogle]], Nobel Laureate in Economics [[Joseph Stiglitz]], the ''[[Washington Post]]'' and others.<ref>[http://www.pay-without-performance.com/ Book webpage]</ref>
