The '''Swedish Standard Industrial Classification''', commonly referred to as '''SNI''', is a Swedish industry standard economic classification system, consisting of a hierarchy of codes that are up to 6-digits long. The most recent version of the SNI standard is '''SNI 2007''', which corresponds to NACE Revision 2.

The SNI standard is modeled on the [[Statistical Classification of Economic Activities in the European Community]], commonly referred to as NACE. The SNI standard is maintained by [[Statistics Sweden]] (also known as SCB), a Swedish government office.<ref>[http://unstats.un.org/unsd/cr/ctryreg/ctrydetail.asp?id=258 United Nations Statistics Division, List of National Classifications, Sweden, SNI 2002]</ref>

